Description_Translated:
EASTER

The first Easter, 3500 years ago, happened the night before the departure of the people of Israel from Egypt.Under God's guidance, Moses instructed the Hebrews that each family chose a lamb, which would be baked and served as food, along with unleavened bread (no yeast) and bitter herbs.

The blood of the lamb would be sprinkled in the portals of the houses, bringing the release of the angel of death to his firstborn.The next day, the people were miraculously saved from the hands of Pharaoh and slavery in Egypt.

From there, Easter would be annually celebrated, recalling this liberation.

But something even bigger would be to come‚Ä¶

Centuries later, the true lamb of God, Jesus Christ, came into the world to surrender in the sacrifice of the cross, pouring out his precious blood for all who believes;For remission of sins‚Ä¶

Jesus was ground for our transgressions, and his resurrection on Sunday was the evidence that his work was not in vain: today the multitude of the saved celebrates the forgiveness and liberation of the captivity of sin.

And the spilled blood still invites the tired and overloaded:
"Come to me, and I will relieve you."

.

.

.

#Easter #VereadorgilSondaAutoSchoa #TempodereFletm

Dando prosseguimento √†s tratativas com o governo, sobre a recomposi√ß√£o das perdas inflacion√°rias e defini√ß√£o da pol√≠tica remunerat√≥ria dos servidores da seguran√ßa p√∫blica, estivemos novamente reunidos hoje (28/03) com o vice-governador, Mateus Sim√µes. 

Em resposta √†s demandas entregues a ele no in√≠cio do m√™s, afirmou que est√° garantida a revis√£o geral anual, referente a 2022. Cobramos, tamb√©m, o pagamento do √≠ndice retroativo, ainda devido √† classe, e a necessidade de se estabelecer, j√° no projeto de lei a ser enviado √† Assembleia Legislativa, uma pol√≠tica remunerat√≥ria para os pr√≥ximos quatro anos, ressaltando que √© preciso esfor√ßo m√°ximo do governo e agilidade nestas quest√µes. 

O vice-governador comprometeu-se a retomar  as discuss√µes com as Secretarias da Fazenda e de Planejamento, para avaliarem qual o compromisso poss√≠vel de ser feito. Um novo encontro ser√° marcado o mais breve poss√≠vel.

Description:
Grande parte das pris√µes do dia 8 de janeiro, foram de averigua√ß√£o, dispositivo abolido com a Constitui√ß√£o da Rep√∫blica de 1988.

EDITORIAL ESTAD√ÉO: Se, por hip√≥tese, o presidente da Rep√∫blica deseja utilizar o Dia Internacional da Mulher para conceder indulto a determinadas mulheres presas,  trata-se de exerc√≠cio de uma compet√™ncia constitucional, de natureza pol√≠tica, pr√≥pria do Poder Executivo. J√° o Judici√°rio n√£o disp√µe dessa  discricionariedade. Ele s√≥ aplica a lei e, no seu exerc√≠cio jurisdicional, evita todo e qualquer ind√≠cio de conota√ß√£o pol√≠tica, como forma de preservar e fortalecer a sua autoridade.‚Å£
‚Å£
Errou, pois, o ministro Alexandre de Moraes, do STF, ao utilizar o 8 de Mar√ßo para soltar 149 mulheres que haviam sido presas por envolvimento nos atos  criminosos de 8 de Janeiro.‚Å£
‚Å£
Ningu√©m discute que essas mulheres deveriam ser soltas. A legisla√ß√£o processual √© cristalina. ‚ÄòA pris√£o preventiva somente ser√° determinada quando  n√£o for cab√≠vel a sua substitui√ß√£o por outra medida cautelar‚Äô, diz o C√≥digo de Processo Penal.‚Å£
‚Å£
O problema foi a soltura sob pretexto do Dia Internacional da Mulher. Ou h√° fundamento legal para algu√©m estar preso ou n√£o h√°, simples assim.‚Å£
‚Å£
No momento em que um juiz solta mulheres por ocasi√£o do 8 de Mar√ßo, h√° a afirma√ß√£o impl√≠cita de que ele tem discricionariedade sobre a liberdade daquelas pessoas. A pris√£o preventiva deixa de ser decorr√™ncia da aplica√ß√£o da lei sobre as circunst√¢ncias concretas de cada pessoa, para tornar-se um ato de vontade do magistrado. No Estado Democr√°tico de Direito, n√£o h√° pris√µes assim; n√£o h√° ju√≠zes com esse poder.‚Å£
‚Å£
Reconhecer excessos ou medidas que fragilizam a autoridade da Justi√ßa n√£o significa desautorizar o trabalho do Judici√°rio, como se o Pa√≠s estivesse sob uma ditadura judicial. ‚Å£
‚Å£
N√£o h√° nada no horizonte que fundamente minimamente essa cr√≠tica. Faz parte do funcionamento normal da Justi√ßa a pr√°tica de erros. E se isso √© assim em situa√ß√µes corriqueiras, a falibilidade √© ainda mais justific√°vel num caso como o do 8 de Janeiro, que envolve muitas pessoas e circunst√¢ncias excepcionais. A quest√£o √© assegurar os meios concretos para que eventuais erros sejam rapidamente corrigidos.
Description_Translated:
Most of the arrests of January 8 were of investigation, a device abolished with the Constitution of the Republic of 1988.

Estad√£o Editorial: If, by hypothesis, the President of the Republic wants to use the International Women's Day to grant pardon to certain prisoners, it is an exercise of a constitutional competence of a political nature, proper to the executive branch.The judiciary does not have this discretion.It only applies the law and, in its jurisdictional exercise, avoids any evidence of political connotation, as a way to preserve and strengthen its authority.‚Å£
‚Å£
Therefore, the STF minister Alexandre de Moraes was wrong when using March 8 to release 149 women who had been arrested for involvement in the criminal acts of 8 January.
‚Å£
No one argues that these women should be released.Procedural legislation is crystal clear.'Preventive arrest will only be determined when its replacement is not appropriate with another precautionary measure', says the Code of Criminal Procedure.‚Å£
‚Å£
The problem was the release under the pretext of International Women's Day.Either there is a legal basis for someone to be stuck or there is, simple as that.‚Å£
‚Å£
By the time a judge releases women on the occasion of March 8, there is the implicit statement that he has discretion about the freedom of those people.Preventive arrest is no longer due to the application of the law on the concrete circumstances of each person, to become an act of will of the magistrate.In the democratic rule of law, there are no arrests like that;There are no judges with this power.‚Å£
‚Å£
Recognizing excesses or measures that weaken the authority of justice does not mean disallowing the work of the judiciary, as if the country were under a judicial dictatorship.‚Å£
‚Å£
There is nothing on the horizon that minimally this criticism.It is part of the normal functioning of justice to practice errors.And if this is so in ordinary situations, bankruptcy is even more justifiable in a case such as January 8, which involves many people and exceptional circumstances.The question is to ensure concrete means so that any errors are quickly corrected.

Recebi do Secret√°rio Rog√©rio Greco os n√∫meros atualizados das promo√ß√µes e progress√µes na carreira dos servidores da SEJUSP referentes a este ano, de diversos cargos e n√≠veis. Fico satisfeito em saber que a situa√ß√£o est√° sendo regularizada e agrade√ßo ao secret√°rio pelo empenho e pelo retorno. Afinal, foram diversas cobran√ßas feitas, por meio de requerimentos de minha autoria, audi√™ncias p√∫blicas da Comiss√£o de Seguran√ßa P√∫blica e tamb√©m no Assembleia Fiscaliza, para que o governo solucionasse a lentid√£o das publica√ß√µes dos atos de promo√ß√£o e progress√£o, bem como regularizasse os respectivos pagamentos, uma vez que as den√∫ncias e reclama√ß√µes dos servidores eram constantes. 

Ao todo, 7.266 servidores - entre Policiais Penais, Agentes Socioeducativos e demais carreiras da SEJUSP - foram beneficiados com os atos publicados em fevereiro e mar√ßo deste ano, sendo 3.252 progress√µes e 4.014 promo√ß√µes. A estimativa para 2023 √© de que 10534 servidores evoluam na carreira, caso preencham os requisitos legais, alcan√ßando 5464 promo√ß√µes e 5070 progress√µes. 

√â importante reconhecer o empenho do Secret√°rio Rog√©rio Greco que n√£o s√≥ est√° regularizando a situa√ß√£o, mas, tamb√©m, tornando p√∫blica as informa√ß√µes, sem que nem mesmo precisemos cobrar. √â gratificante saber que contribu√≠mos para fazer justi√ßa a milhares de servidores que vinham sendo prejudicados em suas carreiras, em raz√£o da morosidade e descaso do estado.
Description_Translated:
I received from Secretary Rog√©rio Greco the updated numbers of promotions and career progressions of Sejusp servers for this year, of various positions and levels.I am pleased to know that the situation is being regularized and I thank the secretary for their commitment and return.After all, there were several charges made, through requests of my own, public hearings of the Public Security Commission and also in the Assembly oversees, so that the government would solve the slowness of publications of promotion and progression acts, as well as regularize their paymentssince the complaints and complaints of the servers were constant.

In all, 7,266 servers - among criminal police, socio -educational agents and other Sejusp careers - benefited from the acts published in February and March this year, 3,252 progressions and 4,014 promotions.The estimate for 2023 is that 10534 servers evolve in their career if they meet legal requirements, reaching 5464 promotions and 5070 progressions.

It is important to recognize the commitment of Secretary Rog√©rio Greco who is not only regularizing the situation, but also making public public public, without even having to charge.It is gratifying to know that we contribute to doing justice to thousands of servers that had been harmed in their careers, due to the slowness and neglect of the state.

Recomposi√ß√£o da perda inflacion√°ria

Estivemos reunidos hoje (06/03) com o vice-governador, Mateus Sim√µes, para cobrar a recomposi√ß√£o das perdas inflacion√°rias dos servidores da seguran√ßa p√∫blica. Em raz√£o do veto do governador √†s parcelas que deveriam ser pagas em 2021 e 2022 - conforme acordo assinado e registrado em ata ‚Äì ainda permanecem com uma defasagem de 35,44%. A reposi√ß√£o √© um direito do servidor, garantido pela Constitui√ß√£o Federal, o que torna obrigat√≥rio que o governo atue dentro da legalidade e cumpra sua obriga√ß√£o. 

Em of√≠cio conjunto, assinado pelos os deputados Sargento Rodrigues, Caporezzo, Delegada Sheila, Coronel Sandro, Junio Amaral e Pedro Aihara. cobramos que a recomposi√ß√£o seja feita com a urg√™ncia necess√°ria, bem como que se estabele√ßa uma pol√≠tica remunerat√≥ria definitiva, colocando fim a essa ang√∫stia e incerteza que, anualmente, atormenta os servidores do executivo. Como representantes eleitos pela classe, estamos unidos e firmes no prop√≥sito de cobrar o cumprimento dos acordos firmados! 

O vice-governador recebeu a reivindica√ß√£o e reconheceu o direito da classe √† recomposi√ß√£o. Ele comprometeu-se a tratar o assunto com as Secretarias de Fazenda e de Planejamento e Gest√£o, j√° deixando agendada, para o pr√≥ximo dia 28, a data para nos reunirmos e darmos andamento √†s tratativas. Tamb√©m participaram da reuni√£o, o Secret√°rio de Justi√ßa e Seguran√ßa P√∫blica, Rog√©rio Greco, o Comandante-geral da PM, Cel. Piassi, o Comandante-geral do BM, Cel. Erlon, e a Delegada-geral Irene Leroy, que responde interinamente pela Chefia da PC.
Description_Translated:
Recomposition of inflationary loss

We have been gathered today (03/06) with the deputy governor, Mateus Sim√µes, to demand the recomposition of the inflationary losses of public safety servants.Due to the governor's veto to the installments that should be paid in 2021 and 2022 - as agreement signed and registered in Minutes - still remain with a lag of 35.44%.The replacement is a right of the server, guaranteed by the Federal Constitution, which makes it mandatory that the government acts within the legality and fulfills its obligation.

In a joint letter, signed by the deputies Sergeant Rodrigues, Caporezzo, Delegate Sheila, Colonel Sandro, Junio Amaral and Pedro Aihara.We demand that the recomposition be done with the necessary urgency, as well as to establish a definitive remuneration policy, ending this anguish and uncertainty that annually plagues the executive's servers.As representatives elected by the class, we are united and firm in order to charge the fulfillment of the agreements signed!

The deputy governor received the claim and recognized the right of the class to recomposition.He pledged to treat the issue with the Treasury and Planning and Management Secretariats, already scheduled, for the 28th, the date to meet and proceed with the negotiations.Also attending the meeting were the Secretary of Justice and Public Security, Rog√©rio Greco, the Commander General of the PM, Cel.Piassi, the Commander General of BM, Cel.Erlon, and the general delegate Irene Leroy, who responds interimly for the head of the PC.

Description:
Na manh√£ de hoje, aproveitei a ida ao 1¬∫ Batalh√£o dos Bombeiros para ver como ficou a instala√ß√£o dos arm√°rios para guardar os equipamentos de prote√ß√£o individual de combate a inc√™ndio, dentre eles os macac√µes antichamas, adquiridos por meio de emenda parlamentar por mim destinada. Por l√°, eles j√° est√£o em uso e deu at√© para sentir o cheiro de fuma√ßa que acaba ficando impregnado, refor√ßando a necessidade e import√¢ncia de que esses arm√°rios sejam para uso individual, em modelo projetado para esta finalidade, evitando a propaga√ß√£o de fuligem e res√≠duos para a roupa pessoal do militar. 

Acompanhado do Comandante-geral, Coronel Erlon, do Comandante e da Ex-comandante do 1¬∫ BBM, Tenente-coronel Giderson Martins e Tenente-coronel Stella Coeli, revisitei a academia de muscula√ß√£o, montada em 2020 com verba que tive a satisfa√ß√£o de destinar, tamb√©m por meio de emenda parlamentar. √â muito bom ver concretizadas as a√ß√µes que planejamos, ao definir a aplica√ß√£o das emendas, e saber que contribu√≠mos para cuidar da sa√∫de f√≠sica e psicol√≥gica dos nossos bombeiros!
Description_Translated:
This morning, I took advantage of the 1st Firefighters Battalion to see how the cabinets were installed to store the Fire Fighting Personal Protective Equipment, including the Anticham Overalls, purchased by means of parliamentary amendment.There, they are already in use and it was even to smell the smoke that ends up being impregnated, reinforcing the need and importance that these cabinets are for individual use, in a model designed for this purpose, avoiding the propagation of soot and wastefor the military's personal clothes.

Accompanied by the commander-general, Colonel Erlon, the commander and former BBM commander, Lieutenant Colonel Gideon Martins and Lieutenant Colonel Stella Coeli, I revisited the Bodybuilding Academy, mounted in 2020 with funds that I was pleased to allocate,also through parliamentary amendment.It is great to see the actions we planned, by defining the application of amendments, and knowing that we contribute to the physical and psychological health of our firefighters!

Description:
Agrade√ßo ao Corpo de Bombeiros de Minas Gerais pelo reconhecimento do meu trabalho e empenho em prol da Corpora√ß√£o e dos servidores. √â uma grande honra ser homenageado durante uma cerim√¥nia t√£o importante e especial, na qual comemoramos os 92 anos do 1¬∞ BBM. Parab√©ns a todos os "Soldados do Fogo" que, ao longo de quase um s√©culo, ajudaram a construir a hist√≥ria de sucesso desta unidade.

Na sequ√™ncia, tive a oportunidade de testemunhar um momento hist√≥rico para o Corpo de Bombeiros, durante a solenidade de Descerramento da foto da Ex-Comandante, Tenente-coronel Stella Coeli, na Sala dos Veteranos. Ela, que foi a primeira mulher a comandar o 1¬∞ BBM, participou do ato ao  lado da Coronel Daniela, tamb√©m primeira mulher a Chefiar o Estado Maior do BM.
Description_Translated:
I thank the Minas Gerais Fire Department for the recognition of my work and commitment to the corporation and the servers.It is a great honor to be honored during such an important and special ceremony, in which we celebrate the 92 years of the 1st BBM.Congratulations to all the "fire soldiers" who, along almost a century, helped build the success story of this unit.

Then I had the opportunity to witness a historic moment to the Fire Department during the solemnity of unveiling the photo of the former commander, Lieutenant Colonel Stella Coeli, in the veteran room.She, who was the first woman to command the 1st BBM, participated in the act next to Colonel Daniela, also the first woman to head the BM Greater State.

Description_Translated:
#Repost @phdelfino
„Éª „Éª „Éª
Yesterday we put the ashes on our fronts, remembering a gesture made since the Old Testament, passing through the days of Jesus, which lasted among the early Christians and that has continued to this day.

"Woe to you, heart! Woe to you, Bethsaida! Because if in shooting and Sidon they had witnessed the miracles that were done in you, they had long been regretted with bag of bag and gray."(Matthew 11, 21)

Ashes have always been a symbol of repentance and penance in the Scriptures.Of public recognition of our sin and the dependence we have of divine grace.

Upon receiving them, we hear from the priest the words with which God rebuked Adam in Genesis: "Remember that you are dust and that you will return to dust."

Initiated to Lent, the Church now invites us to forty days of intense reflection and mortification in preparation for the great day of the liturgical calendar: the Passover of Our Lord.It is only in confrontation with death that we have the exact notion of the priorities and hierarchies of this life.It is in meditation on this reality, that one day we will return to the dust unexpectedly, that we can fulfill what Jesus asked us: ‚ÄúIf anyone wants to come after me, renounce himself, ** Take your cross of each day **and follow me. ‚Äù

Let us not seek Christianity without cross!We don't run from our crosses.These are the opportunities to follow Christ on a daily basis, for as he said: Loving friends is easy, even atheists love‚Ä¶ We only have some merit when we contradict the logic.The Christian is called to what seems crazy in the eyes of the unbelievers: it is to have peace in the midst of chaos, to find happiness in suffering, to perform in service to others, to win when it is donated, to put yourself last, to make yourself small...

As St. Paul said (1 Cor. 1:23): "We preach the Christ *crucified *, which is a scandal for the Jews and madness to the Greeks."

In fact, not everyone will have the grace to understand this madness, this scandal.But whoever understands it‚Ä¶ Ah, this one is halfway through the way to heaven.

I don't know which cross you have in your life today, but whatever, take it with joy.For Christ.Just as he took the biggest of all for you.

Est√° aprovado em 1¬∫ turno, pelo Plen√°rio, o Projeto de Lei 993/19, de minha autoria, que estabelece diretrizes para as a√ß√µes do Estado voltadas para a prote√ß√£o e defesa civil, preven√ß√£o e mitiga√ß√£o dos efeitos de acidentes e atos violentos nas escolas da rede p√∫blica de ensino do Estado. O objetivo √© que o poder p√∫blico incentive a inclus√£o dos princ√≠pios de prote√ß√£o e defesa civil nos curr√≠culos escolares, bem como estabele√ßa medidas de seguran√ßa contra desastres em escolas situadas em √°reas de risco, com a√ß√µes como pesquisas sobre o tema, realiza√ß√£o de campanhas educativas, participa√ß√£o da sociedade e a articula√ß√£o entre os sistemas municipais e estadual de ensino e a Coordenadoria Estadual de Defesa Civil na implementa√ß√£o das a√ß√µes. 

A proposta foi aprovada na forma do substitutivo apresentado pela Comiss√£o de Educa√ß√£o, Ci√™ncia e Tecnologia que acrescentou, ao texto original, diretrizes e a√ß√µes para prevenir efeitos de acidentes e atos violentos nas escolas, como o incentivo √† cria√ß√£o de brigadas de emerg√™ncia e o desenvolvimento de atividades de capacita√ß√£o e treinamento de alunos e profissionais da educa√ß√£o.

Description_Translated:
The first round is approved by the Plenary, Bill 993/19, of my own, which establishes guidelines for state actions aimed at protection and civil defense, prevention and mitigation of the effects of accidents and violent acts in schools of schoolsState Education Network.The objective is for the public power to encourage the inclusion of the principles of protection and civil defense in school curricula, as well as establish security measures against disasters in schools located in risk areas, with actions such as research on the subject, conducting educational campaigns,Participation of the company and the articulation between the municipal and state education systems and the State Civil Defense Coordination in the implementation of actions.

The proposal was approved in the form of the substitute presented by the Education, Science and Technology Commission that added, to the original text, guidelines and actions to prevent effects of accidents and violent acts in schools, such as encouraging emergency brigades and developmentof training and training activities of students and education professionals.

The project returns to the commissions, to look for 2nd round.

Description_Translated:
The Military Police Command concluded the adjustments to put into practice the new rules on the dissemination of service scales and compliance with the weekly and monthly workload of the police, established in ¬ß¬ß 3 and 5 of art.15 of State Law No. 5,301/1969, the Statute of the Military, included by LC 168/22.The regulation is in the circular memorandum no.01.5/2023-DRH, published on the last day 09.

Art.15

I will be attentive and supervise compliance with the law!

Essa √© uma antiga demanda da classe, de extrema import√¢ncia para a sa√∫de da tropa. Os arm√°rios s√£o para uso individual e t√™m um modelo projetado para esta finalidade, evitando a propaga√ß√£o de fuligem para a roupa pessoal do militar. 

Com a emenda de R$ 1.471 milh√£o foram adquiridos 604 unidades, que v√£o atender aos batalh√µes da capital e RMBH. O objetivo inicial era atender, individualmente, todos os bombeiros da √°rea operacional, segundo c√°lculos apresentados pela corpora√ß√£o √† √©poca, mas o aumento do custo dos arm√°rios inviabilizou alcan√ß√°-lo neste primeiro momento. Today, I had the pleasant satisfaction of making symbolic delivery to our firefighters from the cabinets to store personal protective equipment, including antholhamine overalls.This is an old demand of the class, extremely important for the health of the troops.Studies point to the damage caused by waste that is impregnated in the uniforms and PPE after the occurrences of fire fighting, so the importance of being stored separately until cleaning is possible.Cabinets are for individual use and have a model designed for this purpose, avoiding the propagation of soot for the military's personal clothing.

This afternoon, I was in a meeting with PMMG Commander General Colonel Piassi to deal with important matters for our police and military firefighters.

Aliquot

I took the concern about the reduction of the rates so that the command intercede with the government to abide by the STF's decision.

In spite of not having the binding effect, unconstitutionality is decreed.Everyone who fits in lawsuits will win with the right to receive what was improperly discounted.

The military's social security contributions should be 8% again and pensioners should not have any payroll charges.This according to the decision of the STF full.

WORKLOAD

I also asked the commander special attention to how much the application of article 4 of Complementary Law 168/2022, mainly on the calculation of compliance with the weekly workload that will be determined at the end of ninety days, the sum that may not exceed one hundred and sixtyHours per month, as well as knowledge of the work scale seven days in advance.
The general command is already making the necessary adaptations to comply with the law.

Soldier/Cable Promotion

Regarding the promotions, provided for in article 20, of Complementary Law No. 168/2022, which provides for the promotion for time of service to the undergraduate degree, I registered with the command that the provision of the Law of Introduction to the Civil Code, subsequent law revokes previous law.Thus, seven -year -old soldiers are entitled to retroactive promotion.In this sense, I asked the commander to redo the understanding of the HRD of the matter and grant the law provided for by law.

Description_Translated:
On January 31, 2023, the newspaper Lupa UOL.com.br, made a report whose title is: Pseudonym Regina Brasil, pastor of Goi√°s used a telegram to coordinate "attacks" in Brasilia.
The title of this report begins with this biased emphasis, as if I were passing through the pseudonym of a woman or as if I was ready to attack the institutions of the rule of democratic law.
.
.

This attempt was evil as it tried to link the figure of my pastor image in undemocratic acts.
.
.
I want to make it clear that I am extremely against blockages, destruction of public buildings and assets.
.
.
We would manifest, peacefully, as we always did, in an orderly way on January 15, 2023.
.
.

And I went to Brasilia for Not√≠ciar what was happening on January 08, 2023 and there were already people who around 1:30 pm, moving to Esplanade of Ministries, followed reporting until there is there!They had already broken some windows and ran slightly so as not to let anything break.
.
.
This behavior of vandalism is not consistent with the behavior of the patriots who were manifesting 70 days ago in an orderly and peaceful manner who profess their faith in God.
.
.
Continuing the reposting of the magnifying glass, we use two figures and with his words we use two nouns, invasion and attacks always in the malicious attempt of a suprase, as if I were a bandit or terrorist.The report continues to think that on January 08 or 15, 2023, a crime led by me or other patriots was premeditated.
.
.
I do not agree with right or left extremists I am not in favor of invasion or coup, but I am in favor of freedom of political manifestation!
.
.
Continues us comments üëáüëáüëáüëá

J√° s√£o 4 anos de sofrimento e tristeza causados pelo rompimento da barragem da Mina C√≥rrego do Feij√£o, em Brumadinho, em 25 de janeiro de 2019. Em respeito a todas as fam√≠lias que tiveram suas vidas, suas hist√≥rias e perspectivas destru√≠das por aquele mar de lama, n√£o podemos deixar que esse crime caia no esquecimento!

Description:
O deputado estadual Sargento Rodrigues (PL) protocolou nesta segunda-feira (23) pedido para que a Assembleia Legislativa de Minas Gerais (ALMG) se re√∫na de forma extraordin√°ria, ainda em janeiro, para investigar a den√∫ncia de que o secret√°rio de Governo, Igor Eto, teria chantageado um coronel da Pol√≠cia Militar.

Segundo o deputado estadual eleito Caporezzo (PL), Eto teria ligado para o coronel Marco Aur√©lio Zancanela e dito que ele n√£o seria nomeado para chefiar o Estado-Maior da Pol√≠cia Militar caso n√£o convencesse o parlamentar a votar no candidato do governo Zema para presidente da ALMG.

Caporezzo fez a den√∫ncia na sexta-feira (20). No s√°bado, veio √† tona um √°udio do pr√≥prio coronel Zancanela enviado a um grupo de mensagens de oficiais do Alto Comando da corpora√ß√£o em que ele repete a den√∫ncia da tentativa de interfer√™ncia de Igor Eto.

A ALMG est√° em recesso parlamentar at√© 31 de janeiro. Por√©m, os deputados podem ser convocados em caso de urg√™ncia ou de interesse p√∫blico relevante pelo presidente da Casa, Agostinho Patrus (PSD). √â necess√°rio que o pedido de Sargento Rodrigues seja assinado por mais 38 deputados.

‚ÄúUma vez convocada a sess√£o, vai permitir o funcionamento das comiss√µes. Enquanto presidente da Comiss√£o de Seguran√ßa P√∫blica, √© nosso dever, diante da gravidade dos fatos, da interfer√™ncia e inger√™ncia direta na elei√ß√£o do Legislativo pelo secret√°rio de Governo, Igor Eto, n√≥s precisamos convocar o secret√°rio de Governo, o coronel Zancanella e convidar o deputado Caporezzo para esclarecer os fatos. A den√∫ncia √© grav√≠ssima‚Äù, afirmou o deputado estadual.

Fonte: @otempo
Image Text: Deputado quer convocar secret√°rio de Zema acusado de chantagear coronel da PM Sargento Rodrigues pediu que ALMG se re√∫na ainda em janeiro para que Igor Eto, coronel Zancanella deputado eleito Caporezzo compare√ßam √† Comiss√£o de Seguran√ßa P√∫blica
Description_Translated:
State Representative Sergeant Rodrigues (PL) filed on Monday (23) request for the Legislative Assembly of Minas Gerais (ALMG) to meet extraordinaryly, still in January, to investigate the complaint that the secretary of government, IgorEto, would have blackmailed a military police colonel.

According to the elected state deputy Caporezzo (PL), Eto would have called Colonel Marco Aur√©lio Zancanela and said that he would not be appointed to head the Military Police Staff if he did not convince the parliamentarian to vote for the Zema government candidate for president ofALMG.

Caporezzo made the complaint on Friday (20).On Saturday, a audio from Colonel Zancanela himself sent to a group of messages from the high command of the corporation in which he repeats the report of interference from Igor Eto.

Almg is in parliamentary recess until January 31st.However, the deputies may be summoned in case of urgency or relevant public interest by the president of the House, Agostinho Patrus (PSD).Sergeant Rodrigues's request is necessary to be signed by 38 deputies.

‚ÄúOnce the session is called, it will allow the commissions to function.As chairman of the Public Security Commission, it is our duty, given the seriousness of the facts, the interference and direct interference in the election of the Legislature by the Secretary of Government, Igor Eto, we need to summon the Secretary of Government, Colonel Zancanella and invite the deputyCaporezzo to clarify the facts.The complaint is very serious, ‚Äùsaid the state deputy.

Source: @Tempo

Today was the day to deliver to the Military Fire Department of Minas Gerais Five rescue vehicles acquired through parliamentary amendment of Deputy Sargento Rodrigues, to the 2021 state budget, in the total amount of R $ 1,350,000.00.The vehicles will be destined to the municipalities of Jo√£o Pinheiro, Diamantina, Montes Claros, Manhua√ßu and Te√≥filo Otoni.The delivery of the keys took place at the Firefighters Academy in Belo Horizonte.

Description_Translated:
First, I want to make it clear that I was not yesterday (01/08) in Brasilia, so I do not appear in video related to the acts that occurred, as some are trying to make it appear.I'm on vacation with my family!

What I did was to comply with one of the videos, with my opinion about the current political situation in Brazil, the partial interference of the judiciary and the connivance of much of the press.Even, I made it clear that I always defended and defended the maintenance of public order, not compromising vandalism and aggression.However, I believe that popular revolt is a consequence of the behavior of the greatest authorities of our country, which are ignoring the appeals of the people for just justice!This is my indignation, as well as most Brazilians.

I repeat: I am not the person of the video and I was not present in a demonstration yesterday (01/08).

I will trigger the judiciary against those who used someone else's video to impute me crimes.

Sergeant Rodrigues - State Deputy by Minas Gerais
